New issue

Opening a new session with given geometry #1882

Open
Kabouik opened this issue Apr 29, 2020 · 3 comments

Comments

Sorry, something went wrong.

Kabouik commented Apr 29, 2020

Is that possible?

What I want to achieve is this:

This is cmus in one session, and cava in a session below it. I open both in just one command line using a .desktop file with this exec:

bash -c "(! pgrep cmus && tilix -e cmus && tilix -a session-add-down -e cava); sleep 0.1 && cmus-remote -q %f"

When executing an audio file, it checks if cmus is open and adds the file to queue, else if cmus is not opened, it will open it in Tilix and add another Tilix session below to run cava. This works well except a session added that way will always take 50% of the available space. Is there a way to specify the number of rows the new session should use, or even better, a percentage of the window height?

I looked into --geometry but it only affects the window size, and action session-down-resize seems to work only in increments of one row.

sta-c0000 commented Jun 14, 2021

You can accomplish this using session profiles.

Simplest way I can think of is to arrange a Tilix session exactly the way you like it, then save the session using:
Shift+Ctrl+S
Give it a name, and save it anywhere you like (since it's not a default).

Then edit the saved JSON file and add the following lines:
under "child1": {:
"overrideCommand": "cmus",
under "child2": {:
"overrideCommand": "cava",

Then tilix can simply be started with:
tilix -s path_to_session.json
